Scottish independent schools maintain a curriculum of academic excellence and this continued in 2018 with another series of outstanding exam results, strengthened by individual and collective success in sport, art, music and other collective efforts.
With over 30,000 students throughout Scotland, these schools, represented by The Scottish Council of Independent Schools (SCIS), aim to provide the best level of service to their students and their parents.
Independent schools aim to prepare pupils for further higher education, career choice and their place in the world as global citizens.
As an education sector capable of developing and adopting a personalised school curriculum, we note that modern languages continue to be a popular and required subject within schools.
Nelson Mandela said, "If you speak to a man in a language that understands, the message will reach his brain.
If you speak to him in his mother tongue, the message will come to his heart."
This is a powerful reminder that we cannot rely solely on English if we want to build trust with people from other countries.
From the results of this year's exams, we can see that the languages are at the top of the graduations, with the highest percentages of success within the independent schools.
68% of students who have studied foreign languages have obtained the highest number of votes.
