North Korea firmly rejects unilateral disarmament without confidence
The Minister of Foreign Affairs of North Korea stated to the UN on Saturday that the maintenance of sanctions was taking up the country's mistrust in the United States, which in such circumstances would have absolutely refused to give up its nuclear weapons unilaterally.
