The four ships of the Baden-Württemberg class ordered by the Military Navy in 2007 will replace the old vessels of the Bremen class.
They will be equipped with a powerful cannon, a range of anti-aircraft and anti-ship missiles as well as some hidden technologies, such as reduced radar, infrared and acoustic markings.
Other important features include longer maintenance periods, in fact it should be possible to use new sinks up to two years away from national ports.
